<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-590-049  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 590 049.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>IBM System User  Oct 1990 p6(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>IBM begins ascent on Summit. (introduction of ES/9000 mainframecomputers) (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>IBM has announced its new line of mainframe computers called theES/9000.andP;  There are 18 models in the range.andP;  The top models arewater-cooled and will be shipped by the third quarter of 1991.andO;The air-cooled lower ranges offer rack mounted technology andincreased speed.andP;  The new mainframes will be using MVS/ESA Version4, VM/ESA 1, and VSE/ESA 1 operating systems supporting 31 bitaddressing.andP;  SystemView, a systems management architecture basedon OSI, SAA and SNA standards, has also been announced.andP;  The newversion of Repository Manager enables programmers to use a remoteinterface to access the host repository.andP;  IBM has also introduceda new protocol called Enterprise Systems Connectivity Architecture(ESCON).andP;  ESCON connects PCs and peripherals by fiber opticsallowing processor and peripheral to be separated by greaterdistances.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   International Business Machines Corp. (Product introduction).andO;Ticker:    IBM.andO;Product:   IBM ES/9000 (Mainframe computer) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionMainframe Computers.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>